[1] PAHO alert, Americas
Date: Thu 7 May 2015 [note date
Source: PAHO [edited]
http://www.paho.org/hq/index.php?option=com_docman&task=doc_view&Itemid=270&gid=30075&lang=en


Epidemiological Alert, Zika virus infection
--------------------------
The Pan American Health Organization (PAHO) / World Health Organization (WHO) recommends its Member States establish and maintain the capacity for Zika virus infection detection, clinical management and an effective public communication strategy to reduce the presence of the mosquito that transmits this disease, particularly in areas where the vector is present.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This has 8 pages of extremely valuable details about case management, vector control and much else. I don't know how ProMED missed reporting this when it was issued. All countries take note. - Mod.JW]

